GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Analogy> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Analogy> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Analogy> ;
    narr:childCount "31"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers the recurring **analogies and metaphors** aswritten reaches for to make abstract positioning concrete. The founder's origin frame casts [narrative as a physics vector](narr:StyleObs_2) from 2012 flocking simulations. Skill-transfer is pitched via pop culture — the [Matrix \"I know Kung Fu\" chip](narr:StyleObs_Analogy_Matrix), recurring across [several](narr:StyleObs_KungFu) [observations](narr:StyleObs_4). Governance and review borrow from engineering and academia: the customer's CTO's unprompted [PR-with-unit-tests metaphor](narr:StyleObs_CustomerCTOPRMetaphor_Analogy), [code as compilation output](narr:StyleObs_Analogy_1), and a collaborator's [peer-review frame](narr:StyleObs_TamarackReview_PeerReviewAnalogy) plus [research-paper citations](narr:StyleObs_Analogy_ResearchPaper). Product identity leans on the [Apple-not-Microsoft opinionated-workflow](narr:StyleObs_OpinionatedWorkflow) contrast and the [book-vs-living-module](narr:StyleObs_AnalogyBookVsModule) pitch. Concrete, colloquial registers appear too — a demo-call prospect's [McDonald picture menu](narr:StyleObs_McDonaldPictureMenu), [plumbing](narr:StyleObservation_Analogy_1), [branch-and-trunk](narr:StyleObs_BranchTrunkAnalogy), and the [optometrist phoropter](narr:StyleObs_Optometrist) for iterative review. The span is rhetorical-device craft: cite the known, assert the upgrade.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_CarfaxSubstackAnalogy> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_MemoryIngestionAsCodeReview> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_2> ;
